  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Describe the feature you would like\n\nCommand used:\r\n```\r\nforge create MyContract.sol:MyContract --etherscan-api-key $POLYGONSCAN_APIKEY --verify\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\nDeployed to: 0XFOO\r\nTransaction hash: 0xTXTXTXTX\r\nStarting contract verification...\r\nWaiting for etherscan to detect contract deployment...\r\nStart verifying contract `0xDEPLOYED` deployed on polygon\r\nError:\r\nCompiler version has to be set in `foundry.toml`. If the project was not deployed with foundry, specify the version through `--compiler-version` flag.\r\n```\r\nWould be ideal to return early from the `Compiler version has to be set` instead of being stuck with a contract that was deployed that you have to reverify after in another step. Guessing it would be about detecting the `--verify` flag and start there.\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
